A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
To urge and request the Port of New Orleans to expeditiously procure additional backup
motors for the Saint Claude Avenue Bridge in New Orleans, Louisiana.
WHEREAS, burned out motors have caused the Saint Claude Avenue Bridge to be
closed to vehicular traffic for extended periods, contributing to traffic jams in Saint Bernard
Parish; and
WHEREAS, the Saint Claude Avenue Bridge is a critical transportation link
connecting Orleans Parish and Saint Bernard Parish and provides an important route for
residents, workers, and commercial traffic traveling between the two parishes; and
WHEREAS, the reliable operation of the bridge’s mechanical systems is essential
to ensuring the safe and efficient movement of vehicular and maritime traffic in the region;
and
WHEREAS, prolonged closures of the Saint Claude Avenue Bridge may also
negatively affect emergency response times, commuter travel, and local economic activity
in surrounding communities; and
WHEREAS, maintaining additional backup motors would allow the Port of New
Orleans to replace failed equipment more quickly and restore bridge operations in a timely
manner, thereby reducing traffic disruptions and improving reliability of this critical piece
of infrastructure.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
urge and request the Port of New Orleans to expeditiously procure additional backup motors
for the Saint Claude Avenue Bridge in New Orleans, Louisiana, to ensure the continued and
sustained movement of vehicular and maritime traffic in the region.
